<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 01 at 3:57PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Calhoun and
southeastern Richland Counties through 445 PM EDT...
At 356 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms near
Hopkins, or 8 miles southeast of Cayce, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Eastover, Congaree National Park, Gadsden, Hopkins, Sandy Run and
Fort Motte.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
